  "commit_message": "Fix test_opaque_obj leaking opaque type registration across tests. (#186005)\n\nOpaque types live in a global registry for the whole process. The registered name is the class's fully qualified name:\n`name = f\"{cls.__module__}.{cls.__qualname__}\"`\n\n`test_opaque_obj` defines a nested `MyInput`, so every invocation registers the same name as `test_export.TestExport.test_opaque_obj.<locals>.MyInput`.\n\nTest generators reuse that body under different method names. The second run fails with:\n`Type '...My",
